   Logo for Taking Center Stage Taking Center Stage
   A Commitment to Standards-Based Education for California's Middle
   Grades Students
   Curriculum > Taking Center Stage

     The 2001 publication Taking Center Stage is designed to help
     California's educators successfully implement standards-based education
     for middle grades students. It provides clear recommendations on how
     schools can align standards, assessment, accountability, and curriculum
     to ensure that all students meet grade-level content standards.
     Executive Summary (pdf)
     Major themes in the publication.
     Recommendations
     Seven key elements and sixteen recommendations for implementing
     standards-based education and supporting student academic achievement.
     Informational Brochure (pdf)
     Overview of the publication and order form. Contact the CDE Press Sales
     Office directly at P.O. Box 271, Sacramento, CA 95812-0271; phone
     800.995.4099; fax 916.323.0823.
     For more information, contact the Middle Grades Office, 428 J Street,
     Second Floor, Sacramento, CA 95814; phone 916.322.1892.
